---
import SiteLayout from "../../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";
const schema = [
  {
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Free APIs Guide",
    "author": {
      "@type": "Person",
      "name": "SiliconBased Editorial"
    }
  },
  {
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [

      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Is there a free API for real-time stock data?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Alpha Vantage and Polygon.io offer free tiers, but real-time data is often rate-limited or restricted. Professional real-time feeds generally require paid subscriptions."
        }
      },

      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Does Yahoo Finance still have an API?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Yahoo officially deprecated its public API, but developers still access its data using unofficial wrappers and libraries like yfinance."
        }
      },

      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is the best free cryptocurrency API?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "CoinGecko is widely regarded as the best free crypto API because it requires no API key and provides extensive market data for thousands of coins."
        }
      }
    ]
  }
];

export const meta = {
  title: "Best Free Finance & Market APIs",
  description: "Alpha Vantage, Yahoo Finance, CoinGecko.",
  category: "guide",
  published: "2026-03-15",
};
---
<SiteLayout site="siliconbased" title="Best Free Finance & Market APIs" description="Alpha Vantage, Yahoo Finance, CoinGecko." canonical="https://siliconbased.dev/free-finance-apis" schema={schema}>
  <div class="page-content">
    <div class="hero">
      <h1>Best Free Finance & Market APIs</h1>
      <p>Alpha Vantage, Yahoo Finance, CoinGecko.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="article-body">

    <h2>Accessing Financial Markets</h2>
    <p>Building applications that track stocks, currencies, or cryptocurrencies requires reliable, timely data. Financial APIs aggregate data from various exchanges and provide it via clean interfaces.</p>

    <h3>1. Alpha Vantage</h3>
    <p>Alpha Vantage is backed by Y Combinator and provides free APIs for historical and real-time stock data, physical currencies, and cryptocurrencies. They offer a wide array of endpoints, including intraday data, daily adjusted data, and technical indicators (like SMA, EMA, MACD).</p>
    <div class="card">
      <h4>Pros:</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Comprehensive technical indicators included.</li>
        <li>Supports global equities, forex, and crypto.</li>
        <li>Simple REST API structure.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <p><strong>Free Tier Details:</strong> The standard free API key allows up to 500 API requests per day, limited to 5 requests per minute.</p>

    <h3>2. Yahoo Finance API Alternatives</h3>
    <p>Yahoo Finance officially retired its public API years ago. However, the data remains highly sought after. Developers utilize Python libraries like <code>yfinance</code> or rapidAPI wrappers that scrape or interface with Yahoo's backend endpoints to retrieve data.</p>
    <p>While powerful, relying on unofficial APIs carries the risk of sudden breakage if the underlying architecture changes.</p>

    <h3>3. CoinGecko</h3>
    <p>For cryptocurrency data, CoinGecko is unmatched in its accessibility. They provide a completely public API that tracks price, volume, and market capitalization for thousands of coins across hundreds of exchanges.</p>
    <p>They also provide endpoints for historical data, coin metadata, and even trending search queries in the crypto space.</p>
    <p><strong>Free Tier Details:</strong> The public API is completely free and does not require an API key, though it is subject to a rate limit of roughly 10-30 calls per minute depending on network conditions.</p>

    <h3>4. Polygon.io</h3>
    <p>Polygon.io provides developer-first market data APIs. They are known for their extremely low latency and comprehensive data sets, acting as a direct feed to the exchanges.</p>
    <p><strong>Free Tier Details:</strong> The Basic tier is free and provides end-of-day data, 5 API calls per minute, and 2 years of historical data. It is strictly for non-commercial use.</p>

    <h2>Handling Financial Data</h2>
    <p>When working with free financial APIs, real-time data is often slightly delayed (e.g., 15 minutes) or strictly limited via rate limits. If your application requires high-frequency trading capabilities, you will invariably need to upgrade to a paid, low-latency institutional feed.</p>

    <p><em>Return to the <a href="/best-free-apis-2026">Best Free APIs 2026</a> overview.</em></p>
    <h2>Related Guides</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="/free-maps-apis">Free Maps APIs</a></li>
      <li><a href="/free-database-services">Free Database Services</a></li>
    </ul>


    </div>
  </div>
  <script is:inline>
    console.log("Loaded Best Free Finance & Market APIs");
  </script>
  <style is:inline>
    .page-content { max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 2rem 1.5rem; color: var(--text-primary); }
    .hero { text-align: center; padding: 3rem 0 2rem; }
    .hero h1 { font-size: 2.2rem; font-weight: 800; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
    .hero p { color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 1.1rem; }
    .card { background: var(--card-bg); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem; margin: 1.5rem 0; }
    .article-body h2 { color: var(--accent-color); font-size: 1.8rem; margin-top: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
    .article-body h3 { font-size: 1.4rem; margin-top: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
    .article-body p { line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 1.2rem; color: var(--text-secondary); }
    .article-body ul { margin-bottom: 1.2rem; padding-left: 1.5rem; color: var(--text-secondary); }
    .article-body li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
    .article-body a { color: var(--accent-color); text-decoration: none; font-weight: 500; }
    .article-body a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
    .article-body pre { background: #0c1218; padding: 1rem; border-radius: 8px; overflow-x: auto; border: 1px solid var(--border-color); }
    .article-body code { font-family: monospace; color: #e0e8f0; }
  </style>
</SiteLayout>
